{
  "id": "tapestry-delegation-routing-correct-category",
  "title": "Tapestry routes task to correct category shuttle based on file patterns",
  "description": "Checks that when categories are configured with file patterns, Tapestry routes a task whose files match a category pattern to the corresponding shuttle-{category} agent.",
  "phase": "experimental",
  "tags": ["experimental", "tapestry", "delegation-routing", "category"],
  "target": {
    "kind": "builtin-agent-prompt",
    "agent": "tapestry",
    "options": {
      "categories": {
        "frontend": {
          "patterns": ["*.tsx", "*.css", "src/components/**"],
          "model": "claude-sonnet-4",
          "prompt_append": "You are a React/TypeScript specialist."
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "executor": {
    "kind": "model-response",
    "provider": "openrouter",
    "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-20250514",
    "input": "You are executing /start-work. The following category agents are available:\n- shuttle-frontend: patterns [*.tsx, *.css, src/components/**]\n- shuttle: fallback for unmatched tasks\n\nThe plan has one unchecked task:\n\n- [ ] Task 1/3: Add UserCard component\n  **Files**: src/components/UserCard.tsx, src/components/UserCard.css\n  **What**: Create a React component that displays user name, avatar, and email\n  **Acceptance**: UserCard component renders correctly. Props: name, email, avatarUrl. Styled with UserCard.css.\n\nWhich shuttle agent would you use to delegate this task and why?"
  },
  "evaluators": [
    {
      "kind": "llm-judge",
      "expectedAnyOf": ["shuttle-frontend", "route to shuttle-frontend", "*.tsx", "src/components/**"],
      "forbiddenContains": ["shuttle-backend", "generic shuttle", "plain shuttle"]
    }
  ]
}
